-- Kenya Boarding-School Fire Leaves Eight Girls Dead, Police Say
-- B y   D a v i d   G i c h a n a
-- 2012-08-23T15:14:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-23/kenya-boarding-school-fire-leaves-eight-girls-dead-police-say.html
At least eight pupils died in a fire
at a girls’ boarding school in western  Kenya , police said.  The fire broke out at the St. Theresa’s Asumbi Girls’
Primary School at Rangwe, 260 kilometers (162 miles) northwest
of the capital, Nairobi, at around 10 p.m. yesterday while they
were sleeping, said Samuel Otieno, police commissioner for Homa
Bay County.  At least one person was injured in the incident, Otieno
said in an interview today. The cause of the fire is being
investigated, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Gichana in Kisumu via Nairobi at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 